1
00:01:51,890 --> 00:01:54,390
The Dragon's Fang has been stolen?

2
00:01:55,220 --> 00:01:57,330
How blasphemous.

3
00:01:57,930 --> 00:01:59,810
Your Majesty, please rest assured.

4
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:02,330
I've already sent men after it.

5
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:50,960
My name is Satoru Mikami.

6
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:53,680
No—it's Rimuru Tempest.

7
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:56,530
I was originally an ordinary human.

8
00:03:56,530 --> 00:04:00,120
An office worker at a major construction company.

9
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:02,230
But I was stabbed to death,

10
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:05,560
and, as you can see, reincarnated as a slime.

11
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:10,090
There's no use dwelling on the reason,

12
00:04:10,090 --> 00:04:13,900
so I've been doing my best to enjoy life as a slime.

13
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:17,240
Before I knew it, I'd made many companions

14
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:21,430
and founded a nation of monsters called "Tempest,"

15
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:23,910
becoming its king.

16
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:29,750
Of course, hostile forces interfered too,

17
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,460
but I overcame those hardships

18
00:04:33,090 --> 00:04:35,800
and eventually became a Demon Lord.

19
00:04:37,050 --> 00:04:40,390
I even pulled off the founding festival I'd longed for.

20
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,270
My dream is a grand one:

21
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:46,020
to build a world where everyone can live happily.

22
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:50,610
And so, today too, my companions and I keep striving.

23
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,570
And right now,

24
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:06,040
we're heading to Elmesia's resort to celebrate the festival's success.

25
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,290
Amazing!

26
00:05:47,540 --> 00:05:52,440
I never imagined the wyvern ship would be this comfortable.

27
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:57,760
So travel can be this relaxing, huh.

28
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,280
Reading manga up in the sky is great too.

29
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,600
And the drinks are all top-notch.

30
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,080
The snacks are all delicious too.

31
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:09,440
Hey, aren't you all a little too relaxed?

32
00:06:10,690 --> 00:06:12,960
And you even invited us along.

33
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:18,190
I'm glad you're all enjoying it.

34
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:23,410
Elmesia, thank you for the invitation.

35
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:27,580
Yeah, you've taken care of us in so many ways.

36
00:06:28,410 --> 00:06:31,230
This is nothing at all.

37
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:33,840
By the way,

38
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:37,800
arranging a whole reward trip—you're quite the good leader.

39
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,610
I really envy you all.

40
00:06:40,930 --> 00:06:44,890
Not at all—I just wanted to have some fun myself.

41
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:48,620
So what's at this resort we're heading to?

42
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,520
Well now...

43
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:54,060
There's a marketplace and a harbor.

44
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:58,030
It's also a famous tourist spot—you're sure to have a great time.

45
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,990
Lord Rimuru, we can see it now.

46
00:07:09,910 --> 00:07:10,960
It's beautiful.

47
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,400
Incredible—it's beyond what I imagined.

48
00:07:14,290 --> 00:07:16,590
I can't wait, Lord Rimuru.

49
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,630
Mm.

50
00:07:37,230 --> 00:07:38,070
Hurry up!

51
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,320
Wait for me!

52
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:47,660
It's a wyvern ship!

53
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:49,120
So cool!

54
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:49,950
Let's go!

55
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:50,580
Yeah!

56
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:22,280
We've been expecting you, Empress Elmesia.

57
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:27,590
Lord Rimuru, please let us know if you need anything.

58
00:08:28,530 --> 00:08:30,830
Thank you for having us.

59
00:08:49,390 --> 00:08:52,720
Looking closely, that dragon really is huge.

60
00:08:53,770 --> 00:08:54,500
Notice.

61
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,270
That dragon is the Guardian Dragon King.

62
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:59,400
Presumed to belong to the Spirit Dragon race.

63
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,530
A Spirit Dragon?

64
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:05,720
That's right—impressive that you recognized it.

65
00:09:06,070 --> 00:09:07,320
So it really is?

66
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:12,330
So Milim's pet dragon that humans killed wasn't the only one after all.

67
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:17,540
Indeed—there are still several of them around.

68
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:23,590
They rarely appear, so they've come to be treated as legends.

69
00:09:30,890 --> 00:09:32,760
My first time at a resort.

70
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:36,310
I'm really hoping for a romantic encounter.

71
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:39,020
This is the entrance to the town.

72
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,960
Everyone, enjoy yourselves freely.

73
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:43,610
Thank you.

74
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,740
There are stalls!

75
00:09:46,740 --> 00:09:48,130
What? Stalls?

76
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,860
No time to waste—let's go!

77
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:52,990
Wait, Milim—don't leave me behind!

78
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:57,160
My, what an impatient one.

79
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,870
I'm so sorry, Elmesia.

80
00:10:00,290 --> 00:10:01,540
It's fine.

81
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:04,650
What are your plans next?

82
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:09,260
I've prepared some treasured wine—I'm off to enjoy it.

83
00:10:09,260 --> 00:10:10,110
Fine wine?

84
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:11,760
I'm coming too.

85
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:14,410
I want to taste your treasured stash.

86
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:18,430
The Empress's treasured wine? What do you think?

87
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:20,100
It's bound to be worth looking forward to.

88
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:23,440
We've got no other plans anyway.

89
00:10:23,650 --> 00:10:25,420
We'll come along too.

90
00:10:25,730 --> 00:10:26,980
Oh my.

91
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,200
Then let's drink to our hearts' content together.

92
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,870
Naturally.

93
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,370
So carefree.

94
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:37,410
Lord Rimuru.

95
00:10:40,330 --> 00:10:43,040
Let's go inspect this island.

96
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:46,170
"Inspect," huh.

97
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,670
Fine, fine, go ahead.

98
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:51,180
I look forward to your results.

99
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:51,800
Yes!

100
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:56,390
So this is the liberating feeling of a resort.

101
00:10:57,010 --> 00:10:58,270
Lord Rimuru.

102
00:10:59,310 --> 00:11:01,190
I want to go to the beach.

103
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:05,570
The beach, huh.

104
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:11,200
Right—it's a rare reward trip.

105
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:13,910
Let's enjoy it to the fullest.

106
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:22,850
You'll be amazed—the sea here is truly beautiful.

107
00:11:23,710 --> 00:11:28,300
Sarion's nobles and guests all come here to vacation.

108
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,420
Eren, have you been here before?

109
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:34,620
Yeah, Ellie brought me here.

110
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:38,310
It'd be nice if the others could come too.

111
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:44,560
Once we're back, let's let those who didn't come take turns visiting.

112
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,750
There's no need at all to bring the Second Secretary.

113
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:50,400
Leaving Lord Rimuru's side—how outrageous.

114
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:53,110
He has no sense of responsibility as a secretary.

115
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:57,220
Do you want him to come or not?

116
00:11:58,330 --> 00:12:01,220
I wonder where Diablo is right now.

117
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,610
You want subordinates?

118
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:08,750
Yes.

119
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:12,780
I'd like subordinates who can help handle odd jobs.

120
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,950
Like brewing tea and such?

121
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,720
No, you misunderstand.

122
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:23,000
Attending to you devotedly is my important duty.

123
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:26,060
What I mean is,

124
00:12:26,690 --> 00:12:33,720
I'd like subordinates to handle chores like destroying nations on my behalf.

125
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:36,220
What is this guy talking about?

126
00:12:36,910 --> 00:12:43,160
I have a few old acquaintances I'd like to go recruit.

127
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:46,290
I ask for your permission.

128
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:52,340
I gave Diablo permission, and then he left.

129
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:52,960
But...

130
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:53,800
But...

131
00:12:54,630 --> 00:12:58,590
I'm so worried about just what kind of people he'll bring back.

132
00:12:58,590 --> 00:12:59,640
Lord Rimuru.

133
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,810
Stop dwelling on that—look, it's the sea!

134
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:05,690
It's huge!

135
00:13:05,690 --> 00:13:07,370
So beautiful!

136
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:30,080
What a wonderful place.

137
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,520
Right?

138
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:35,920
Wonderful.

139
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:41,550
It really is a wonderful place.

140
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:43,220
Yeah.

141
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:46,290
Lord Rimuru.

142
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:49,270
Won't you come play?

143
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,920
It feels great!

144
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,280
Sure, coming right up.

145
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:05,330
Rimuru Tempest!

146
00:14:14,710 --> 00:14:15,760
Take this!

147
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:19,510
Honestly, Lord Rimuru.

148
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:21,180
That won't work.

149
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:23,680
You're something else.

150
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:26,180
Over here.

151
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,060
Lord Rimuru, what's wrong?

152
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:39,530
What is that?

153
00:14:42,450 --> 00:14:44,950
Awesome!

154
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:46,520
Lady Ramiris, please show some restraint.

155
00:14:46,830 --> 00:14:48,290
It's fine!

156
00:14:57,050 --> 00:14:58,710
Where did it come flying from?

157
00:14:58,710 --> 00:14:59,550
Who cares.

158
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,550
That light...

159
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:06,430
Notice.

160
00:15:06,850 --> 00:15:08,520
Presumed to be Nuclear Strike magic.

161
00:15:08,930 --> 00:15:11,020
No effect on this island.

162
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:12,690
I see.

163
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:17,270
I'd better hurry.

164
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:23,010
An attack is incoming!

165
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,990
Issue an emergency alert nationwide!

166
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,930
Everyone, protect your heads!

167
00:15:57,940 --> 00:15:59,820
What in the world was that?

168
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,220
Notice.

169
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:04,410
Besides the impact point of the Nuclear Strike magic,

170
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:07,470
another epicenter has been detected.

171
00:16:08,990 --> 00:16:10,240
Another one?

172
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:15,880
So that's the rumored...

173
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,380
Leon really has it rough.

174
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:22,240
By Leon, you mean the Demon Lord Leon Cromwell?

175
00:16:23,170 --> 00:16:24,360
Yes.

176
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:27,340
Why bring up Lord Leon?

177
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:32,350
His territory, the Golden Land of Eldorado, is near here.

178
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:35,480
But someone keeps playing pranks on them.

179
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:37,350
Pranks?

180
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,900
Apparently they're often attacked by Nuclear Strike magic,

181
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:43,720
and Demon Lord Leon deflects it with a protective barrier.

182
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:47,570
What a huge nuisance.

183
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:50,970
The people on this island won't be affected, will they?

184
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:53,410
I've heard there's no problem.

185
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:58,420
He makes the Nuclear Strike magic land out in the open sea, so it won't affect this island.

186
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:03,610
Leon has always been careful about that.

187
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,610
The islanders say they've grown used to it.

188
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:12,600
What's for dinner tonight?

189
00:17:14,890 --> 00:17:16,350
That's good, then.

190
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:22,400
Still, who would dare pull pranks on a Demon Lord?

191
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:34,390
A complete waste of effort.

192
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:38,870
Does that demon never grow tired of it?

193
00:17:41,170 --> 00:17:44,920
It's become a regular sight to the residents now.

194
00:17:45,970 --> 00:17:47,840
It's such a headache.

195
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:57,830
Djeese! Where is Djeese?

196
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:01,400
I'm here.

197
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,270
Djeese.

198
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:05,990
At this rate, our nation will collapse.

199
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:10,640
Has the Water Dragon still not awakened?

200
00:18:11,410 --> 00:18:14,950
We're still searching for the stolen Dragon's Fang.

201
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:22,040
What are you all doing? We desperately need the Water Dragon's power now!

202
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:26,840
I've already dispatched Zodon—please wait a little longer.

203
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,190
So many goods on display!

204
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:47,210
What souvenirs should we get for the others?

205
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:50,200
How about it? Dazzling, isn't it?

206
00:18:54,780 --> 00:18:56,040
So cute!

207
00:18:58,120 --> 00:19:00,210
Maybe let's pick this as a gift.

208
00:19:00,210 --> 00:19:01,250
So adorable.

209
00:19:02,290 --> 00:19:03,960
How exquisite.

210
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:06,250
They're handmade by the islanders.

211
00:19:07,090 --> 00:19:09,240
I suppose this is a source of income for them too.

212
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:12,720
There are cute hair ornaments over there too.

213
00:19:13,140 --> 00:19:16,260
Can't we just grab any old souvenir?

214
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,600
Absolutely not.

215
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:21,060
Let's go, Gobta.

216
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,310
All right.

217
00:19:38,370 --> 00:19:40,450
Wait, wait, wait, little lady!

218
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:42,120
You've come to the right place.

219
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:44,770
Buy now and you get this for free!

220
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:56,100
Lord Djeese, we've found her.

221
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,780
We're moving in.

222
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,890
Mm. Don't disappoint me.

223
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:07,770
Where did she go?

224
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,300
Halt!

225
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,450
Do you have business with Lord Rimuru?

226
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:19,240
Sorry, I have no idea what you're talking about.

227
00:20:22,790 --> 00:20:24,460
Playing dumb won't help you.

228
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:29,020
You've been following us this whole time, haven't you?

229
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:33,110
You've got the wrong person.

230
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:43,850
Let me through!

231
00:20:44,060 --> 00:20:46,980
I can't let a suspicious person pass.

232
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:51,780
Who are you calling suspicious?

233
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:58,450
I'm a local fisherman's daughter.

234
00:20:58,450 --> 00:21:01,390
A fish—fisherman's daughter, huh? What of it?

235
00:21:01,580 --> 00:21:04,560
What I mean is, I have zero interest in you people.

236
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:07,830
Y-You'd better come clean right now.

237
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:09,500
Right, Lord Rimuru?

238
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:13,880
He's gone.

239
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:17,630
Lord Rimuru is gone!

240
00:21:18,890 --> 00:21:20,140
This is bad.

241
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:23,270
Hey, how are you going to make this up to me?

242
00:21:23,270 --> 00:21:26,190
What else can we do but go look for him?

243
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,270
Lord Rimuru!

244
00:21:29,310 --> 00:21:32,130
Wait, don't just run off on your own!

245
00:21:41,620 --> 00:21:44,540
Almost there—just a little more.

246
00:21:57,670 --> 00:21:59,570
How long are you going to keep following me?

247
00:22:00,590 --> 00:22:02,890
We just happen to be going the same way.

248
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:04,770
Is that so?

249
00:22:06,850 --> 00:22:08,100
Wh-What are you doing?

250
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,140
Nothing.

251
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:22,910
What's wrong? You can go on ahead.

252
00:22:29,370 --> 00:22:31,810
What is this creature?

253
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:43,140
So cute, so cute!

254
00:22:44,390 --> 00:22:46,270
All fluffy.

255
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:49,600
Don't leave me behind.

256
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:56,480
One moment you tell me to go, the next you won't let me.

257
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,940
So selfish.

258
00:22:58,570 --> 00:23:01,070
By the way, is this the right way?

259
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:02,840
How would I know?

260
00:23:03,370 --> 00:23:06,700
Aren't you an islander? How do you not know?

261
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:15,040
You know, I bet your master has already forgotten about you.

262
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:17,340
You don't look very capable anyway.

263
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:22,340
I'll have you know I'm one of Tempest's Four Heavenly Kings,

264
00:23:22,340 --> 00:23:23,590
Gobta!

265
00:23:25,470 --> 00:23:26,700
Four Heavenly Kings?

266
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:30,480
That's right—so there's no way I'd be forgotten.

267
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:34,650
Lord Rimuru must be searching all over for me right now.

268
00:23:37,770 --> 00:23:39,650
I should be able to find him from here.

269
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:55,500
Next up is the island's proudest attraction.

270
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,520
The stalactite cave exploration tour.

271
00:23:59,050 --> 00:24:00,510
Sounds fun.

272
00:24:00,510 --> 00:24:01,340
Yeah.

273
00:24:02,170 --> 00:24:04,470
Welcome to the stalactite cave exploration tour.

274
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,030
How many in your party?

275
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,660
Four people.

276
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:14,060
Looks like he really did forget about you.

277
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:16,560
Lord Rimuru...

278
00:24:17,810 --> 00:24:20,110
Oh no, I'm going to lose them again.

279
00:24:21,150 --> 00:24:22,190
Hurry up.

280
00:24:22,610 --> 00:24:23,450
Wait.

281
00:24:28,030 --> 00:24:29,970
So beautiful.

282
00:24:30,950 --> 00:24:33,250
It puts my mind at ease.

283
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,630
It's like being in another world.

284
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:39,980
Legend says

285
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:47,010
a couple who reach this cave's exit together will stay together forever.

286
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:51,810
Welcome to the stalactite cave exploration tour.

287
00:24:52,020 --> 00:24:53,270
How many in your party?

288
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:56,600
One person.

289
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,150
That makes two, then.

290
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:03,690
Have a safe trip.

291
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,280
It's gorgeous, isn't it, Lord Rimuru?

292
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:09,320
Quite fun.

293
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:12,660
Lord Rimuru, let's build one in Tempest too.

294
00:25:17,670 --> 00:25:19,750
Got to catch up to them at full speed.

295
00:25:19,750 --> 00:25:21,900
This way—it's definitely this way.

296
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:38,310
Lord Rimuru!

297
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:41,860
Ugh, you're in the way.

298
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:43,940
I can't help it—it's too cramped.

299
00:25:44,990 --> 00:25:47,220
You should've waited to ride the next seal.

300
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:50,200
How could I let you go ahead of me?

301
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:52,700
"You, you"—so annoying!

302
00:25:52,910 --> 00:25:54,370
My name is Yura.

303
00:25:55,830 --> 00:25:57,850
I'm Gobta.

304
00:25:59,370 --> 00:26:02,500
Stalactite donuts!

305
00:26:03,550 --> 00:26:04,590
Oh, right.

306
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:05,420
Ranga!

307
00:26:18,770 --> 00:26:19,810
Want more?

308
00:26:20,230 --> 00:26:22,110
Don't be shy—eat up, eat up.

309
00:26:23,570 --> 00:26:24,820
Many thanks.

310
00:26:32,740 --> 00:26:34,830
I really lost them.

311
00:26:43,790 --> 00:26:44,650
There was something just now.

312
00:26:44,650 --> 00:26:45,670
Hey.

313
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,760
Don't touch me in weird places!

314
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:48,590
What are you trying to do, pervert—I didn't—

315
00:26:50,050 --> 00:26:51,930
What are you so worked up over?

316
00:26:51,930 --> 00:26:53,390
Shut up.

317
00:26:53,390 --> 00:26:55,060
Who do you think I—

318
00:27:27,170 --> 00:27:28,420
Ow...

319
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:29,460
Are you okay?

320
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,590
You'd better not move around.

321
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:42,600
You're not hurt, are you?

322
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:47,820
Aren't I a suspicious person?

323
00:27:48,860 --> 00:27:50,320
Why would you save me?

324
00:27:53,450 --> 00:27:54,700
Well...

325
00:27:55,320 --> 00:27:57,620
You don't need a reason to save someone.

326
00:28:00,020 --> 00:28:02,410
All right, let's go find the exit.

327
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,880
I'd have been fine on my own.

328
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:12,010
I'm glad you weren't hurt.

329
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:14,090
I'm never coming here again.

330
00:28:15,970 --> 00:28:16,800
How's it going?

331
00:28:18,050 --> 00:28:19,100
Haven't caught her yet.

332
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:22,020
Useless—what are you doing?

333
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,310
I'm sorry.

334
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:27,440
Just the flute will do—hurry and get it back.

335
00:28:29,110 --> 00:28:30,150
As you command.

336
00:28:31,820 --> 00:28:34,950
It feels like we've wandered into another world.

337
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:38,700
This area is a maze—be careful, okay?

338
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,990
It's just like a labyrinth—how thrilling!

339
00:28:40,990 --> 00:28:41,830
A labyrinth...

340
00:28:43,270 --> 00:28:44,750
I accept the challenge.

341
00:28:45,370 --> 00:28:47,770
It's not like there are enemies here.

342
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:50,020
Lord Rimuru, there's a fork.

343
00:28:52,260 --> 00:28:54,550
All right, let's take the left.

344
00:28:55,590 --> 00:29:00,180
Exploring unknown paths—that's the joy of travel.

345
00:29:01,850 --> 00:29:05,790
Lord Rimuru, where are you?

346
00:29:06,230 --> 00:29:09,770
Honestly, now I've got no leads at all.

347
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:12,800
So, are you really one of the Four Heavenly Kings?

348
00:29:13,740 --> 00:29:14,550
Of course.

349
00:29:15,610 --> 00:29:17,070
I'm an executive, you know.

350
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:19,570
Really? That's pretty impressive.

351
00:29:26,670 --> 00:29:27,920
Which way should we go?

352
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:32,500
When you're lost, go right.

353
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,840
Are you sure it's this way?

354
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:38,340
Are you even listening?

355
00:29:45,020 --> 00:29:46,690
You know the mission, right?

356
00:29:49,810 --> 00:29:51,480
A little roughness is fine.

357
00:29:51,690 --> 00:29:52,520
Yes.

358
00:29:58,990 --> 00:30:00,030
Yura?

359
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:06,710
They've already tracked us this far?

360
00:30:13,170 --> 00:30:14,000
Gobta.

361
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,670
So you noticed too.

362
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:19,840
Why are they chasing us?

363
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:30,480
Let her go!

364
00:31:17,610 --> 00:31:18,440
Are you okay?

365
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:19,900
I let my guard down.

366
00:31:25,330 --> 00:31:26,160
Gobta!

367
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:28,040
You saved me.

368
00:31:28,450 --> 00:31:30,330
You've got some moves yourself.

369
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:39,920
Those guys are way too persistent.

370
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:42,010
Why are they after us?

371
00:32:00,990 --> 00:32:01,510
What?

372
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:15,850
If you just cooperate, no one has to get hurt.

373
00:33:32,740 --> 00:33:33,580
Yura!

374
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:36,290
Zodon.

375
00:33:53,810 --> 00:33:54,640
Damn it, she's gone.

376
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,730
Did we lose them?

377
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:34,530
To make me groan like this...

378
00:35:34,950 --> 00:35:37,660
You've got quite the skill.

379
00:35:37,870 --> 00:35:39,330
Oh my.

380
00:35:39,750 --> 00:35:42,040
Lady Ramiris, can you taste the difference?

381
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,290
What's that supposed to mean?

382
00:35:43,290 --> 00:35:45,590
Want to fight? Bring it on!

383
00:35:48,710 --> 00:35:51,840
Lady Ramiris, Lady Frey is over there.

384
00:35:56,850 --> 00:35:58,930
It seems a bit noisy around here.

385
00:35:59,770 --> 00:36:00,600
Is it?

386
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:04,150
Yeah, I'm a little curious about it too.

387
00:36:04,150 --> 00:36:05,810
I didn't even notice.

388
00:36:05,810 --> 00:36:09,980
Idiot, it's obviously the rumble of the Nuclear Strike magic.

389
00:36:09,980 --> 00:36:13,110
Right, there was that.

390
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,620
Then there's nothing to worry about.

391
00:36:15,820 --> 00:36:18,530
Lady Ramiris, what would you like to drink next?

392
00:36:18,530 --> 00:36:20,200
Let me think...

393
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:23,540
Lady Ramiris, maybe you should stop drinking.

394
00:36:32,300 --> 00:36:33,760
We should be safe here.

395
00:36:36,890 --> 00:36:38,970
I never knew the sunset was this beautiful.

396
00:36:44,190 --> 00:36:45,440
It's gorgeous.

397
00:36:46,690 --> 00:36:48,360
Yeah.

398
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:54,820
So this is what a real sunset looks like.

399
00:36:55,860 --> 00:36:57,470
Why is it so red?

400
00:36:58,780 --> 00:37:00,660
I could watch it forever and never tire.

401
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:03,370
Right?

402
00:37:05,870 --> 00:37:10,150
The old me never looked up at the sky like this.

403
00:37:11,300 --> 00:37:15,470
Just dealing with what was right in front of me took everything I had.

404
00:37:16,700 --> 00:37:19,430
I never had room to enjoy the scenery.

405
00:37:20,890 --> 00:37:22,140
Is that so.

406
00:37:22,970 --> 00:37:26,310
So all you have to do is look up, and you can see such beauty.

407
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:31,880
Now I've taken another step toward becoming someone great.

408
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:37,010
Oh dear.

409
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:41,740
So sorry to spoil your mood.

410
00:37:43,620 --> 00:37:44,600
They tracked us all the way here?

411
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:49,250
Lady Yura, please come back to the kingdom with us.

412
00:38:05,730 --> 00:38:07,290
Gobta, over here!

413
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:08,440
Hurry, come on!

414
00:38:08,850 --> 00:38:10,960
No good—it's impossible.

415
00:38:22,830 --> 00:38:23,450
What?

416
00:38:25,750 --> 00:38:26,580
Gobta!

417
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:28,460
Yura!

418
00:39:00,150 --> 00:39:01,050
Yura!

419
00:39:01,610 --> 00:39:04,330
Yura, can you hear me? Yura!

420
00:39:04,330 --> 00:39:05,580
Calm down.

421
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:08,500
She's just unconscious.

422
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:11,830
Let's take her somewhere she can rest quietly first.

423
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,860
Gobta, you should go rest too.

424
00:39:37,690 --> 00:39:38,730
Lord Rimuru...

425
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:43,530
Don't worry, she'll wake up soon.

426
00:39:45,410 --> 00:39:47,290
I guess...

427
00:40:16,850 --> 00:40:23,620
O living things of the sea,

428
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:32,870
weaving together their wishes,

429
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:43,600
tiny bodies nestled close to one another,

430
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:49,100
swimming onward through the waves,

431
00:40:49,100 --> 00:40:54,320
within the swirling eddies,

432
00:40:54,320 --> 00:41:00,540
tears scatter, foam dissolves away,

433
00:41:00,540 --> 00:41:05,540
the light of life

434
00:41:05,980 --> 00:41:11,020
will turn into stars,

435
00:41:11,020 --> 00:41:15,800
guiding the way forward,

436
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:21,390
setting out on the eternal road.

437
00:41:24,010 --> 00:41:29,780
The flowing tides of time and the deep blue sea—

438
00:41:29,780 --> 00:41:34,640
the bonds they carry brought us together.

439
00:41:34,640 --> 00:41:45,420
The voice we pass on will never cease.

440
00:41:46,410 --> 00:41:50,490
Thoughts of peace and prayers for the future,

441
00:41:50,490 --> 00:42:00,180
entrusted to this song, entrusted to the One who awakens,

442
00:42:00,180 --> 00:42:06,810
entrusting everything.

443
00:42:15,140 --> 00:42:18,480
The Water Dragon...

444
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:24,840
I've got it.

445
00:42:29,110 --> 00:42:31,200
Well done, Zodon.

446
00:42:34,740 --> 00:42:36,620
Begin preparations immediately.

447
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,910
As you command.

448
00:42:43,290 --> 00:42:45,730
Be quicker about it next time.

449
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:52,890
How is she?

450
00:42:57,480 --> 00:42:59,140
Still asleep.

451
00:43:00,190 --> 00:43:01,020
I see.

452
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:07,070
Where did Djeese go? Has the Water Dragon still not awakened?

453
00:43:08,940 --> 00:43:10,200
I'm right here.

454
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:11,930
Djeese.

455
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:12,910
Where's Yura?

456
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:16,040
And the Dragon's Fang? What's the status of the Water Dragon?

457
00:43:16,450 --> 00:43:21,560
I've already retrieved the Dragon's Fang from her, as you can see.

458
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:23,540
That's our Djeese.

459
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:27,570
But the Dragon's Fang can only be used by the priestess, no?

460
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,590
The analysis is already complete.

461
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:34,240
To me, it's nothing more than a simple little mechanism.

462
00:43:39,160 --> 00:43:41,620
Notice. Nuclear Strike magic detected.

463
00:43:45,650 --> 00:43:47,320
This is the revelation.

464
00:43:47,730 --> 00:43:52,740
I shall now use this flute to command the Water Dragon.

465
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:54,820
Watch closely, all of you.

466
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,820
What's going on?

467
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:29,210
This is bad!

468
00:44:29,210 --> 00:44:30,070
Veldora!

469
00:44:30,070 --> 00:44:31,940
Right, leave it to me.

470
00:44:50,090 --> 00:44:51,480
What's next?

471
00:44:56,340 --> 00:44:57,600
What's wrong?

472
00:44:57,800 --> 00:45:00,310
Scared because I'm too strong?

473
00:45:01,770 --> 00:45:03,230
What was that just now?

474
00:45:03,230 --> 00:45:05,310
It looked like a dragon.

475
00:45:06,350 --> 00:45:07,400
Yura!

476
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:21,160
My name is Yura. I'm the priestess of the Kingdom of Kaien.

477
00:45:21,580 --> 00:45:22,620
Priestess?

478
00:45:22,620 --> 00:45:23,660
Kingdom of Kaien?

479
00:45:24,500 --> 00:45:29,290
It's the undersea nation from the island's legends, right?

480
00:45:30,130 --> 00:45:35,700
As I recall, it once had friendly relations with this island.

481
00:45:37,220 --> 00:45:40,140
Does this have something to do with that dragon just now?

482
00:45:42,430 --> 00:45:46,390
That dragon is the Water Dragon, the guardian deity of the Kingdom of Kaien.

483
00:45:49,310 --> 00:45:54,110
Someone awakened the Water Dragon, intending to attack the surface.

484
00:45:54,300 --> 00:45:55,300
Attack the surface?

485
00:45:57,450 --> 00:46:01,830
Come to think of it, the Kingdom of Kaien's chancellor is Djeese.

486
00:46:02,030 --> 00:46:03,060
Isn't that right?

487
00:46:04,950 --> 00:46:07,060
And you are...?

488
00:46:09,120 --> 00:46:11,560
I am Elmesia El Ru Sarion.

489
00:46:12,670 --> 00:46:13,360
The Empress?

490
00:46:15,170 --> 00:46:18,300
Let's get back to the point—there's more to this, right?

491
00:46:18,930 --> 00:46:20,390
Y-Yes.

492
00:46:21,220 --> 00:46:26,020
With my power alone, I cannot stop Djeese.

493
00:46:27,270 --> 00:46:30,400
I came to the surface seeking help.

494
00:46:30,810 --> 00:46:33,320
But the situation back home only worsened.

495
00:46:34,570 --> 00:46:38,740
Lord Rimuru, I beg you—I want to help Yura.

496
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:41,030
I want to do something.

497
00:46:41,030 --> 00:46:44,370
But this is so sudden.

498
00:46:44,990 --> 00:46:48,540
Then I'll formally issue the request.

499
00:46:50,420 --> 00:46:55,210
Could you head to the Kingdom of Kaien and resolve this problem?

500
00:47:00,220 --> 00:47:04,030
Don't tell me—you invited us here precisely so that...

501
00:47:04,600 --> 00:47:06,470
What are you talking about?

502
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:10,920
Still, the free things are the most expensive of all.

503
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:15,860
Then let's take a trip to the seafloor.

504
00:47:15,860 --> 00:47:17,110
To the Kingdom of Kaien.

505
00:47:17,740 --> 00:47:19,340
I'll help you, Yura.

506
00:47:25,450 --> 00:47:27,120
Thank you so much.

507
00:47:36,090 --> 00:47:39,210
Rimuru, why are you leaving me behind?

508
00:47:40,050 --> 00:47:41,090
Veldora, my friend.

509
00:47:41,720 --> 00:47:45,680
Only the strongest can protect this place from being caught in the Nuclear Strike magic.

510
00:47:46,930 --> 00:47:47,770
The strongest?

511
00:47:47,770 --> 00:47:48,620
That's right.

512
00:47:48,810 --> 00:47:52,080
And when it comes to the strongest, that's you, of course, Veldora my friend.

513
00:47:52,560 --> 00:47:54,960
You're the only one I can entrust this to with peace of mind.

514
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:57,150
Well, then I have no choice.

515
00:47:57,150 --> 00:47:59,230
After all, I am the strongest.

516
00:48:01,320 --> 00:48:02,340
Then let's get going.

517
00:48:02,340 --> 00:48:03,820
Milim, you stay too.

518
00:48:04,660 --> 00:48:08,200
But I want to come along too!

519
00:48:09,450 --> 00:48:10,910
Milim...

520
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:12,580
What a shame.

521
00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:16,960
There happen to be Master Yoshida's delicious desserts here, though.

522
00:48:17,380 --> 00:48:18,840
Really?

523
00:48:19,250 --> 00:48:20,300
Let's go eat them together!

524
00:48:20,510 --> 00:48:23,430
I want some too!

525
00:48:23,430 --> 00:48:24,780
Then it's settled.

526
00:48:29,470 --> 00:48:33,230
I'm really grateful to Frey.

527
00:48:33,440 --> 00:48:36,980
If we brought those two along, they'd probably destroy the whole city.

528
00:48:41,780 --> 00:48:43,860
What exactly is the Water Dragon...?

529
00:48:45,530 --> 00:48:49,700
Our ancestors once lived on the surface too.

530
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:50,950
But

531
00:48:51,580 --> 00:48:55,310
they despised war and sought a place to live in peace,

532
00:48:55,960 --> 00:48:57,420
wandering everywhere.

533
00:48:58,820 --> 00:49:06,800
It was the Water Dragon and its messenger who granted them a kingdom beneath the sea.

534
00:49:07,640 --> 00:49:11,080
After that, the Water Dragon fell into a long slumber.

535
00:49:12,220 --> 00:49:15,350
And my family was granted a flute.

536
00:49:16,600 --> 00:49:20,980
That flute lets the user's heart connect with the Water Dragon, right?

537
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:22,030
Yes.

538
00:49:22,860 --> 00:49:25,150
Ever since, we've lived in peace.

539
00:49:26,610 --> 00:49:31,200
But a few decades ago, things changed.

540
00:49:32,660 --> 00:49:34,120
The Nuclear Strike magic...

541
00:49:38,080 --> 00:49:43,090
The Kingdom of Kaien is caught in the Nuclear Strike magic every single day.

542
00:49:46,010 --> 00:49:48,090
I heard the Nuclear Strike magic lands out in the open sea.

543
00:49:48,090 --> 00:49:49,550
Does it affect you too?

544
00:49:50,390 --> 00:49:51,430
But, but...

545
00:49:51,640 --> 00:49:55,200
I'd think Leon would avoid harming others.

546
00:49:56,020 --> 00:49:58,310
All of this seems to be Djeese's scheme.

547
00:49:59,150 --> 00:50:04,150
The Nuclear Strike magic itself lands in a place that doesn't affect the Kingdom of Kaien.

548
00:50:05,820 --> 00:50:06,240
However...

549
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:06,650
However...

550
00:50:12,910 --> 00:50:16,040
Djeese triggers a separate explosion near the Kingdom of Kaien,

551
00:50:16,250 --> 00:50:19,170
making everyone believe the Nuclear Strike magic struck the Kingdom of Kaien.

552
00:50:19,370 --> 00:50:21,610
Come to think of it, the King of Wisdom said something...

553
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:22,860
Notice.

554
00:50:22,860 --> 00:50:25,010
Besides the impact point of the Nuclear Strike magic,

555
00:50:25,420 --> 00:50:28,110
another epicenter was detected.

556
00:50:28,340 --> 00:50:30,840
So that's what it meant.

557
00:50:31,680 --> 00:50:34,810
Djeese is the Kingdom of Kaien's chancellor, right?

558
00:50:36,060 --> 00:50:38,770
He's hailed as the most brilliant genius since the kingdom's founding.

559
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:42,110
He studied the surface's civilization and culture,

560
00:50:42,520 --> 00:50:45,650
and dramatically improved our lives.

561
00:50:46,900 --> 00:50:50,130
If Djeese says so, then it must be true.

562
00:50:51,490 --> 00:50:56,290
That was a preliminary strike by the Demon Lord to invade our nation.

563
00:50:56,500 --> 00:50:57,750
What?

564
00:50:57,960 --> 00:51:00,040
Before long,

565
00:51:00,250 --> 00:51:03,590
the Demon Lord Rimuru will lead the vanguard and launch a full-scale assault.

566
00:51:04,210 --> 00:51:06,300
Why are you so certain?

567
00:51:09,420 --> 00:51:12,700
Because I've captured one of the Demon Lord's subordinates.

568
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:29,030
The Demon Lord Rimuru said he'd slaughter everyone here.

569
00:51:29,240 --> 00:51:32,780
To find this place, he's been blasting the whole area with magic.

570
00:51:32,990 --> 00:51:35,080
He'll be attacking soon.

571
00:51:41,330 --> 00:51:44,440
Your Majesty, I have an idea.

572
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:46,520
Oh? Let's hear it, Djeese.

573
00:51:48,010 --> 00:51:51,740
We need only awaken the Water Dragon.

574
00:51:53,430 --> 00:51:55,300
Is that even possible?

575
00:51:55,720 --> 00:51:58,430
If we study the ancient texts, perhaps it can be done.

576
00:51:58,850 --> 00:51:59,830
But that's forbidden.

577
00:52:00,310 --> 00:52:02,390
The nation is on the verge of ruin.

578
00:52:02,600 --> 00:52:03,750
This...

579
00:52:04,480 --> 00:52:06,250
This is all for the Kingdom of Kaien.

580
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:10,740
Lady Yura, you mustn't.

581
00:52:11,360 --> 00:52:12,260
Lady Yura.

582
00:52:13,660 --> 00:52:15,950
Please make your decision.

583
00:52:20,950 --> 00:52:24,710
If this can save the Kingdom of Kaien, then so be it.

584
00:52:46,190 --> 00:52:47,650
Is something the matter?

585
00:52:47,860 --> 00:52:51,610
It's nothing—not really a problem.

586
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:55,360
The Demon Lord Rimuru is about to visit a nearby island.

587
00:52:57,030 --> 00:52:58,490
It'll be fine, won't it?

588
00:52:58,700 --> 00:53:02,040
I hear he's a pushover—he'll be easy to handle.

589
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:04,960
As expected of Lord Djeese.

590
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:07,880
And our payment?

591
00:53:08,090 --> 00:53:09,130
Don't worry.

592
00:53:09,750 --> 00:53:12,050
But there's one more thing I need you to do.

593
00:53:12,260 --> 00:53:13,920
Just pay us enough.

594
00:53:18,510 --> 00:53:19,970
I see.

595
00:53:23,730 --> 00:53:26,650
But even if the Water Dragon is powerful,

596
00:53:26,850 --> 00:53:31,130
declaring war on a Demon Lord is too unrealistic, isn't it?

597
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:35,760
No, not necessarily.

598
00:53:36,240 --> 00:53:37,280
Indeed.

599
00:53:37,910 --> 00:53:42,700
If the Water Dragon's true nature is as I suspect,

600
00:53:46,670 --> 00:53:51,670
then it's perhaps no wonder it would dream such a foolish dream.

601
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:26,290
This melody is lovely.

602
00:54:27,850 --> 00:54:33,110
It's a prayer song dedicated to the Water Dragon.

603
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:37,550
It's usually played on the flute.

604
00:54:39,630 --> 00:54:40,890
Gobta...

605
00:54:42,550 --> 00:54:43,600
I'm sorry.

606
00:54:45,890 --> 00:54:48,190
I used you.

607
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:51,730
No, no, no—you had no choice either.

608
00:54:52,150 --> 00:54:55,280
And I doubted you too.

609
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:57,570
I'm sorry.

610
00:55:12,790 --> 00:55:19,670
The Water Dragon's power is meant to protect all living things in the sea.

611
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:23,850
But he wants to use the Water Dragon to wage war.

612
00:55:24,470 --> 00:55:26,140
You've got me here.

613
00:55:26,770 --> 00:55:30,310
As long as the great Gobta is around, there's nothing to worry about.

614
00:55:33,020 --> 00:55:34,480
How reliable.

615
00:55:44,700 --> 00:55:48,060
I've been waiting, Lady Yura.

616
00:55:49,500 --> 00:55:51,580
That voice is... Djeese!

617
00:55:53,880 --> 00:55:55,960
Behold, King Litt.

618
00:55:56,380 --> 00:55:58,320
Just as I said.

619
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:01,590
The Water Dragon priestess Yura stole the flute,

620
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:04,570
and even guided the surface's vanguard here.

621
00:56:06,180 --> 00:56:10,200
She actually intended to bring surface dwellers into the Kingdom of Kaien.

622
00:56:10,770 --> 00:56:12,850
Lady Yura betrayed us?

623
00:56:12,850 --> 00:56:15,210
Lady Yura would never do such a thing.

624
00:56:15,770 --> 00:56:17,860
Then is Lord Djeese lying?

625
00:56:17,860 --> 00:56:19,320
How could that be?

626
00:56:21,190 --> 00:56:23,700
Djeese, show yourself!

627
00:56:27,660 --> 00:56:28,290
The flute's sound...

628
00:56:31,620 --> 00:56:35,380
Notice. A massive energy reaction detected on the seafloor.

629
00:56:36,420 --> 00:56:37,250
Don't tell me...

630
00:56:42,670 --> 00:56:43,860
It's the Water Dragon!

631
00:56:48,510 --> 00:56:49,560
Djeese?

632
00:56:53,310 --> 00:56:58,940
I'll destroy the traitor Yura, along with the invaders' vanguard.

633
00:56:58,940 --> 00:57:01,650
You have no right to hold that flute.

634
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:04,780
What nonsense.

635
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:09,160
That only the priestess's bloodline can play it is mere superstition.

636
00:57:09,370 --> 00:57:12,910
The flute's master doesn't have to be you.

637
00:57:13,640 --> 00:57:15,000
However,

638
00:57:15,210 --> 00:57:20,210
it's true that only those with sufficient magicules can use it.

639
00:57:20,840 --> 00:57:21,940
But

640
00:57:22,300 --> 00:57:25,360
I can play it.

641
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:34,810
Here it comes!

642
00:57:44,610 --> 00:57:45,450
Gobta!

643
00:57:45,450 --> 00:57:46,280
Lord Rimuru!

644
00:57:49,300 --> 00:57:50,870
King of Gluttony!

645
00:57:58,790 --> 00:58:00,460
You all stay here.

646
00:58:58,020 --> 00:59:00,940
How about it? What a wondrous power.

647
00:59:01,150 --> 00:59:04,690
I truly don't understand why it was never used.

648
00:59:05,110 --> 00:59:06,340
Djeese...

649
00:59:07,610 --> 00:59:13,140
You all faithfully obeyed the rules and never read the ancient texts, did you?

650
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:17,830
The ancient texts also recorded a use like this.

651
01:00:08,510 --> 01:00:11,840
Damn it, this monster!

652
01:00:52,090 --> 01:00:53,130
The Water Dragon!

653
01:00:54,180 --> 01:00:55,070
Yura!

654
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:00,640
Lord Rimuru, let's go too.

655
01:01:00,640 --> 01:01:02,370
Right, let's go.

656
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:42,330
We're saved.

657
01:01:42,970 --> 01:01:44,020
Hold on tight.

658
01:02:02,140 --> 01:02:03,140
Yura!

659
01:02:15,090 --> 01:02:17,070
Yura!

660
01:02:34,900 --> 01:02:35,940
Yura!

661
01:02:36,990 --> 01:02:38,860
Yura?

662
01:02:46,370 --> 01:02:48,670
It's all right now.

663
01:02:57,010 --> 01:02:57,990
The flute...

664
01:03:04,720 --> 01:03:07,640
Notice. The Water Dragon has vanished.

665
01:03:31,830 --> 01:03:36,630
Demon Lord Rimuru, welcome.

666
01:03:37,050 --> 01:03:41,220
It's an honor to meet you as well, King Litt.

667
01:03:42,260 --> 01:03:47,270
Our nation has given great offense; I hardly know how to atone.

668
01:03:47,470 --> 01:03:49,140
There's no need to atone.

669
01:03:49,770 --> 01:03:52,120
As long as nothing happens from now on, it's fine.

670
01:04:07,080 --> 01:04:07,910
What is this?

671
01:04:10,620 --> 01:04:16,040
Our ancestors painted this when they first settled here.

672
01:04:17,090 --> 01:04:18,960
That's the Kingdom of Kaien.

673
01:04:19,590 --> 01:04:21,670
Are the lines below the water currents?

674
01:04:23,340 --> 01:04:25,220
That's you, isn't it, Yura?

675
01:04:27,310 --> 01:04:28,770
No, that's...

676
01:04:29,180 --> 01:04:33,980
It depicts the Water Dragon and its messenger granting us the flute.

677
01:04:34,190 --> 01:04:34,710
Huh?

678
01:04:35,230 --> 01:04:38,360
You were definitely trying to get Yura's attention, weren't you?

679
01:04:38,570 --> 01:04:41,070
I get you, Gobta.

680
01:04:41,280 --> 01:04:43,990
But she just said the ancestors painted it.

681
01:04:43,990 --> 01:04:45,240
Good point.

682
01:04:46,490 --> 01:04:47,950
I spoke too hastily.

683
01:04:48,160 --> 01:04:50,450
But it really does look like Yura.

684
01:04:51,700 --> 01:04:52,540
I'm flattered.

685
01:04:59,630 --> 01:05:01,090
How mysterious.

686
01:05:02,550 --> 01:05:04,630
It's remarkably well preserved.

687
01:05:07,140 --> 01:05:07,760
Notice.

688
01:05:08,180 --> 01:05:12,350
Presumed to be ruins, equipped with all manner of facilities.

689
01:05:19,230 --> 01:05:21,730
Lady Yura!

690
01:05:21,730 --> 01:05:22,780
Welcome back.

691
01:05:22,780 --> 01:05:24,240
We're so glad you're safe.

692
01:05:24,240 --> 01:05:27,570
I believed in you from the very start.

693
01:05:27,570 --> 01:05:29,450
You and your sweet talk.

694
01:05:33,830 --> 01:05:34,870
Lady Yura.

695
01:05:35,080 --> 01:05:37,580
Lady Yura, play the flute like always.

696
01:05:37,580 --> 01:05:38,940
I want to hear it, I want to hear it!

697
01:05:41,960 --> 01:05:44,880
Actually, the flute is broken.

698
01:05:48,430 --> 01:05:51,620
Even though the flute's broken, we still have the memory shells.

699
01:05:52,180 --> 01:05:53,330
Memory shells?

700
01:05:54,060 --> 01:05:57,810
If you channel sound into that kind of conch, it records it.

701
01:05:58,230 --> 01:05:59,900
It can do that too, huh.

702
01:06:03,860 --> 01:06:06,360
I can hear Lady Yura's flute.

703
01:06:09,490 --> 01:06:11,370
Please rest here tonight.

704
01:06:12,620 --> 01:06:15,120
I still have matters to attend to, so I'll head back to the palace.

705
01:06:15,960 --> 01:06:18,400
Yuri, Mio, I'll leave the rest to you.

706
01:06:20,540 --> 01:06:21,380
This way, please.

707
01:06:21,790 --> 01:06:23,670
See you later, then, Yura.

708
01:06:36,180 --> 01:06:38,270
Damn it, damn it!

709
01:06:39,730 --> 01:06:42,860
Cursed Yura—I'll make you pay dearly.

710
01:06:45,780 --> 01:06:47,240
Zodon.

711
01:06:47,650 --> 01:06:49,740
What took you so long? Where were you?

712
01:06:49,950 --> 01:06:52,660
Why are you only rescuing me now? So slow!

713
01:07:12,470 --> 01:07:13,300
Zodon...

714
01:07:14,760 --> 01:07:16,640
How dare you...

715
01:07:17,270 --> 01:07:19,980
Damn it, damn it, damn it!

716
01:07:20,190 --> 01:07:23,730
How dare a lowly wretch like you do this to me!

717
01:07:24,150 --> 01:07:27,170
I won't forgive you—I will never forgive you!

718
01:07:37,500 --> 01:07:38,230
What's happening?

719
01:07:39,580 --> 01:07:41,040
You're the slow one.

720
01:08:12,320 --> 01:08:15,660
Go on—you're worried about her, aren't you?

721
01:08:18,580 --> 01:08:20,140
Thank you.

722
01:08:26,500 --> 01:08:28,590
What's gotten into Gobta?

723
01:08:29,840 --> 01:08:30,880
It's nothing.

724
01:10:08,900 --> 01:10:14,940
All my life, I've lived for the kingdom and its people.

725
01:10:16,820 --> 01:10:19,530
Seeing everyone's smiles is my happiness.

726
01:10:21,830 --> 01:10:26,000
But sometimes, I can't even catch my breath.

727
01:10:29,750 --> 01:10:33,920
Whenever that happens, I secretly come here to watch the stars.

728
01:10:35,380 --> 01:10:36,010
The stars?

729
01:10:41,010 --> 01:10:43,310
Ever since we were entrusted with the flute,

730
01:10:44,140 --> 01:10:48,100
my family has prayed for the Kingdom of Kaien.

731
01:10:52,900 --> 01:10:57,490
The messenger told our ancestors that as long as they kept offering prayers to the Water Dragon,

732
01:10:58,110 --> 01:11:02,490
it would grant them a home beneath the sea.

733
01:11:04,370 --> 01:11:09,170
The Water Dragon lives on people's faith, on their prayers.

734
01:11:10,100 --> 01:11:14,380
But the people who once offered prayers began to fight among themselves,

735
01:11:14,800 --> 01:11:16,670
and in the end, no one prayed anymore.

736
01:11:18,970 --> 01:11:23,970
Our ancestors accepted the terms and were allowed to settle here.

737
01:11:24,810 --> 01:11:28,560
After that, the Water Dragon fell into a long slumber.

738
01:11:29,190 --> 01:11:32,940
And the people of the Kingdom of Kaien kept offering their prayers.

739
01:11:34,610 --> 01:11:36,900
Our family, as priestesses,

740
01:11:37,110 --> 01:11:41,700
are charged with channeling those prayers into the flute's sound and conveying them to the Water Dragon.

741
01:11:46,700 --> 01:11:50,660
But now both the flute and the Water Dragon are...

742
01:11:52,330 --> 01:11:54,000
I mustn't lose heart.

743
01:11:56,020 --> 01:11:59,630
Sorry for letting you see me in such a pathetic state.

744
01:11:59,840 --> 01:12:01,510
It's not pathetic at all.

745
01:12:04,430 --> 01:12:08,390
We goblins used to be super weak.

746
01:12:10,060 --> 01:12:12,980
But then we met Lord Rimuru,

747
01:12:13,400 --> 01:12:15,060
and we've fought side by side ever since.

748
01:12:15,900 --> 01:12:19,240
Former enemies have now become comrades.

749
01:12:19,440 --> 01:12:21,950
And together we built a nation.

750
01:12:23,610 --> 01:12:25,700
The people of the Kingdom of Kaien are comrades too.

751
01:12:26,120 --> 01:12:27,990
I'll help too.

752
01:12:29,660 --> 01:12:33,210
And Lord Rimuru will help as well.

753
01:12:34,880 --> 01:12:36,270
So everything will be fine.

754
01:12:39,260 --> 01:12:41,130
Thank you, Gobta.

755
01:12:46,350 --> 01:12:48,220
What a wonderful place.

756
01:12:48,430 --> 01:12:50,100
The food is delicious too.

757
01:12:50,310 --> 01:12:51,350
Yeah.

758
01:12:55,310 --> 01:12:56,980
Did Gobta get to see her?

759
01:13:01,780 --> 01:13:03,650
I should head back.

760
01:13:10,540 --> 01:13:12,350
Everyone will worry.

761
01:13:28,620 --> 01:13:30,560
I've come for you.

762
01:13:32,020 --> 01:13:34,710
Water Dragon priestess, Yura.

763
01:13:35,140 --> 01:13:36,000
Zodon!

764
01:13:41,820 --> 01:13:42,440
Ow!

765
01:13:42,650 --> 01:13:43,690
Yura!

766
01:13:43,690 --> 01:13:44,950
A mere goblin.

767
01:13:46,200 --> 01:13:46,820
Gobta!

768
01:13:47,030 --> 01:13:48,490
Know your place.

769
01:13:50,580 --> 01:13:52,450
A bug that just won't die.

770
01:13:58,710 --> 01:14:00,790
Go feed the sharks.

771
01:14:07,680 --> 01:14:08,720
Gobta!

772
01:14:31,870 --> 01:14:33,950
Lord Rimuru! Lord Rimuru!

773
01:14:36,460 --> 01:14:37,500
Lord Rimuru!

774
01:14:38,750 --> 01:14:40,210
Yuri and Mio?

775
01:14:40,630 --> 01:14:41,460
What's wrong?

776
01:14:41,880 --> 01:14:42,920
Lady Yura, she...

777
01:14:43,130 --> 01:14:45,210
Lady Yura still hasn't come back.

778
01:14:45,630 --> 01:14:46,670
Yura?

779
01:14:46,880 --> 01:14:49,180
Gobta went to find her just now.

780
01:15:01,900 --> 01:15:02,940
Lord Rimuru?

781
01:15:10,450 --> 01:15:11,680
Master, look over there.

782
01:15:16,910 --> 01:15:17,750
Gobta!

783
01:15:21,080 --> 01:15:21,920
Gobta!

784
01:15:30,470 --> 01:15:32,340
L-Lord Rimuru...

785
01:15:35,890 --> 01:15:38,180
Yura... Yura's in danger.

786
01:15:47,570 --> 01:15:49,240
What happened to Yuri and Mio?

787
01:15:49,650 --> 01:15:51,320
Was this Djeese's doing too?

788
01:15:52,160 --> 01:15:53,200
Djeese...

789
01:15:55,280 --> 01:15:57,370
He's nothing but a reject.

790
01:15:58,410 --> 01:16:00,910
I've been lending him power all along, leading him on.

791
01:16:01,330 --> 01:16:04,250
Yet he never noticed—what a fool.

792
01:16:04,670 --> 01:16:05,920
What are you talking about?

793
01:16:06,960 --> 01:16:11,130
Besides, I never laid a hand on your attendants.

794
01:16:12,380 --> 01:16:15,300
That was a lie to make you come quietly.

795
01:16:17,390 --> 01:16:20,750
Bringing me to a place like this—just what are you after?

796
01:16:22,600 --> 01:16:26,150
I'm going to hold a wedding for you and me.

797
01:16:27,190 --> 01:16:29,490
My wife, Yura.

798
01:16:31,360 --> 01:16:36,780
As long as we live together, we'll surely rule the whole world.

799
01:16:37,200 --> 01:16:39,700
Everything will be mine.

800
01:16:40,120 --> 01:16:43,310
Your body and heart, your power—all of it will be mine.

801
01:16:43,870 --> 01:16:45,130
Power?

802
01:16:45,750 --> 01:16:47,570
What power do I even have left now?

803
01:16:48,050 --> 01:16:52,220
What I need is your body.

804
01:16:53,680 --> 01:16:54,510
That's right.

805
01:16:54,930 --> 01:17:00,350
Only one person can draw out the power sleeping deep within your body.

806
01:17:00,560 --> 01:17:03,060
And that's me—your husband.

807
01:17:08,070 --> 01:17:09,530
There's no need to resist.

808
01:17:10,150 --> 01:17:13,700
Relax, and give your body over to me.

809
01:17:14,740 --> 01:17:17,240
Th-This feeling is...

810
01:17:18,700 --> 01:17:20,580
No way—I can feel it.

811
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:23,080
The Water Dragon is right beside me.

812
01:17:23,710 --> 01:17:24,960
This can't be.

813
01:17:32,670 --> 01:17:34,550
Wh-What was that just now...?

814
01:17:34,970 --> 01:17:37,890
The Water Dragon's... memories?

815
01:17:38,930 --> 01:17:41,430
It really does look like Yura.

816
01:17:42,890 --> 01:17:46,230
I understand now—so that's how it is.

817
01:17:47,900 --> 01:17:48,310
I...

818
01:18:01,240 --> 01:18:02,910
The search party is ready.

819
01:18:03,120 --> 01:18:03,950
We'll set out at once—

820
01:18:05,830 --> 01:18:06,460
Notice.

821
01:18:06,670 --> 01:18:10,840
A powerful energy has been detected on the seafloor of the Kingdom of Kaien.

822
01:18:11,670 --> 01:18:12,500
Is it the Water Dragon?

823
01:18:20,010 --> 01:18:20,850
Yura?

824
01:18:20,850 --> 01:18:21,680
Zodon?

825
01:18:22,310 --> 01:18:24,040
So Zodon was the mastermind behind it all.

826
01:18:25,020 --> 01:18:26,890
The Water Dragon is about to revive.

827
01:18:27,310 --> 01:18:29,190
The flute is already broken, isn't it?

828
01:18:29,610 --> 01:18:32,730
The power to commune with the Water Dragon doesn't come from the flute.

829
01:18:33,150 --> 01:18:35,030
It comes from Yura herself.

830
01:18:36,070 --> 01:18:38,360
Yura has already become my wife.

831
01:18:38,990 --> 01:18:41,070
I'll keep her by my side and dote on her.

832
01:18:42,120 --> 01:18:46,910
So that I may rule this world forever.

833
01:18:51,290 --> 01:18:52,340
What's going on?

834
01:18:53,170 --> 01:18:55,880
Notice. The Kingdom of Kaien is beginning to move.

835
01:18:55,880 --> 01:18:56,920
What?

836
01:19:07,350 --> 01:19:07,980
What's wrong?

837
01:19:07,980 --> 01:19:09,330
What's happening?

838
01:19:11,520 --> 01:19:13,610
At this rate, the chains will break.

839
01:19:30,710 --> 01:19:31,750
What is that?

840
01:19:31,750 --> 01:19:33,980
It doesn't look like Nuclear Strike magic.

841
01:19:35,920 --> 01:19:38,010
This seems bad.

842
01:19:38,630 --> 01:19:39,680
It would appear so.

843
01:19:40,090 --> 01:19:43,640
This is the Water Dragon's Light of the End.

844
01:19:43,850 --> 01:19:44,470
Let's go.

845
01:19:49,690 --> 01:19:50,730
Lord Rimuru.

846
01:19:51,140 --> 01:19:52,190
Where's the Water Dragon?

847
01:19:52,400 --> 01:19:53,020
Over there.

848
01:20:00,950 --> 01:20:02,610
It's heading for the island!

849
01:20:03,240 --> 01:20:04,700
Let's give it a try first.

850
01:20:09,290 --> 01:20:10,750
King of Gluttony!

851
01:20:14,610 --> 01:20:15,340
Did I get it?

852
01:20:15,750 --> 01:20:19,780
Notice. The substance devoured was nothing but seawater.

853
01:20:20,130 --> 01:20:21,170
Seawater?

854
01:20:21,590 --> 01:20:23,050
Lord Rimuru, look!

855
01:20:27,430 --> 01:20:29,000
The seawater turned into the Water Dragon?

856
01:20:32,440 --> 01:20:34,730
This is the true power of the Water Dragon.

857
01:20:35,560 --> 01:20:39,110
All seawater can become its body.

858
01:20:39,940 --> 01:20:43,070
As long as the ocean exists, it will never die.

859
01:20:43,910 --> 01:20:45,430
Hey, hey, you've got to be kidding.

860
01:20:45,990 --> 01:20:50,680
Even a Demon Lord couldn't dry up the entire ocean.

861
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:54,750
If you actually did that, the world would be destroyed.

862
01:20:55,790 --> 01:20:58,440
Seems the enemy is trickier than expected.

863
01:20:59,130 --> 01:21:02,050
Rejoice, you trash of the Kingdom of Kaien.

864
01:21:02,260 --> 01:21:05,180
I grant you permission to die for me.

865
01:21:06,010 --> 01:21:08,100
Become a part of the Water Dragon.

866
01:21:16,650 --> 01:21:17,480
Calm down.

867
01:21:17,690 --> 01:21:18,940
Please stay calm.

868
01:21:19,360 --> 01:21:21,650
The Kingdom of Kaien is starting to surface.

869
01:21:21,860 --> 01:21:22,690
What?

870
01:21:35,000 --> 01:21:37,500
Guide the residents to the shelters.

871
01:21:39,170 --> 01:21:40,000
Hurry!

872
01:21:40,000 --> 01:21:41,250
Faster!

873
01:21:41,670 --> 01:21:44,380
Ramiris, can you teleport them into the labyrinth?

874
01:21:44,380 --> 01:21:45,840
Always asking the impossible.

875
01:21:45,840 --> 01:21:48,970
There are too many conditions I can't meet—I can't do it!

876
01:21:59,190 --> 01:22:00,440
Is that all?

877
01:22:00,860 --> 01:22:03,780
Begone—Spirit Particle Slash!

878
01:22:06,700 --> 01:22:08,010
Back me up, Gobta!

879
01:22:15,870 --> 01:22:17,750
Watch out—it's headed your way!

880
01:22:18,580 --> 01:22:20,040
I see it.

881
01:22:20,460 --> 01:22:21,710
Leave this side to us.

882
01:22:22,820 --> 01:22:24,010
Let's go.

883
01:22:24,210 --> 01:22:25,260
Treyni!

884
01:22:25,670 --> 01:22:26,720
Beretta!

885
01:22:26,720 --> 01:22:28,180
Yes, Lady Ramiris.

886
01:22:41,730 --> 01:22:42,250
Too slow.

887
01:22:42,250 --> 01:22:44,210
Thousand-Thread Demon Slash!

888
01:22:57,890 --> 01:23:00,500
Evaporate—Black Flame Hell!

889
01:23:05,610 --> 01:23:07,380
That's number 34.

890
01:23:07,380 --> 01:23:10,510
Number 35.

891
01:23:20,310 --> 01:23:23,020
Let's go, my wife.

892
01:23:29,490 --> 01:23:30,220
Is that...?

893
01:23:42,420 --> 01:23:43,880
It's Yura.

894
01:23:58,270 --> 01:23:59,520
Why is this happening?

895
01:24:02,230 --> 01:24:04,730
Give Yura back!

896
01:24:09,530 --> 01:24:10,570
Gobta?

897
01:24:25,790 --> 01:24:28,090
Wait for me, Yura!

898
01:24:41,230 --> 01:24:42,270
Gob—

899
01:24:44,150 --> 01:24:47,070
Yura!

900
01:24:50,190 --> 01:24:51,240
Gobta!

901
01:25:10,630 --> 01:25:14,180
As expected of my wife, my Water Dragon.

902
01:25:14,590 --> 01:25:17,930
Even a Demon Lord is no threat.

903
01:25:27,110 --> 01:25:28,570
Such overwhelming power.

904
01:25:31,070 --> 01:25:32,530
Yura...

905
01:25:52,340 --> 01:25:53,280
How could this be?

906
01:25:53,280 --> 01:25:55,050
There's no end to it.

907
01:25:55,880 --> 01:25:57,550
What in the world is going on?

908
01:26:00,160 --> 01:26:05,270
Yura, your flesh and blood all belong to me.

909
01:26:07,250 --> 01:26:09,440
Become one with me.

910
01:26:42,600 --> 01:26:47,390
Yura, your power is now mine to command.

911
01:26:49,060 --> 01:26:50,940
Let's become gods together.

912
01:27:04,700 --> 01:27:05,540
That island...

913
01:27:08,040 --> 01:27:10,540
Let's start with that island.

914
01:27:12,210 --> 01:27:14,710
I shall conquer the world.

915
01:27:26,390 --> 01:27:28,060
Singing?

916
01:27:32,860 --> 01:27:34,940
Yura...

917
01:27:35,750 --> 01:27:37,650
It's Yura's voice, singing.

918
01:27:42,030 --> 01:27:42,660
Gobta.

919
01:27:44,530 --> 01:27:47,660
Ranga, let's go save Yura!

920
01:27:47,250 --> 01:27:47,830
Call upon me!

921
01:27:48,080 --> 01:27:48,910
Right!

922
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:51,830
Gobta.

923
01:27:52,040 --> 01:27:52,670
Notice.

924
01:27:52,880 --> 01:27:55,170
Detecting the wavelength of the individual designated Yura.

925
01:27:55,380 --> 01:27:56,210
What?

926
01:27:57,670 --> 01:28:01,840
It's likely the individual designated Zodon has deployed a special barrier.

927
01:27:57,990 --> 01:28:03,390
Don't be impatient—it's not yet time to fret.

928
01:28:03,390 --> 01:28:08,290
Well done—cross the breathtaking azure sea.

929
01:28:06,220 --> 01:28:07,270
Cover me!

930
01:28:08,290 --> 01:28:13,200
Now, enduring these tangled emotions,

931
01:28:12,690 --> 01:28:17,690
How could you not obey me, my wife?

932
01:28:13,200 --> 01:28:17,280
searching for a place to stir my sinking thoughts,

933
01:28:17,280 --> 01:28:27,290
I call your name, so you may hear this song.

934
01:28:19,990 --> 01:28:20,820
Yura?

935
01:28:26,870 --> 01:28:27,910
Ranga!

936
01:28:28,190 --> 01:28:31,720
Striking down my own cowardice,

937
01:28:30,830 --> 01:28:32,500
Demon Wolf Fusion!

938
01:28:31,720 --> 01:28:36,930
if I have the courage to raise my well-honed fist against the trial, it's fine even if I get hurt.

939
01:28:36,930 --> 01:28:38,430
I know what it means to be strong.

940
01:28:38,430 --> 01:28:41,630
When the moment comes, I'll be ready.

941
01:28:41,630 --> 01:28:45,730
Before I fade away, I make a firm vow:

942
01:28:45,730 --> 01:28:46,730
to protect you.

943
01:28:46,730 --> 01:28:50,170
Don't wound my heart or body, and I can coexist with you.

944
01:28:50,170 --> 01:29:00,760
Following the shining light's guidance, I seek a radiant vision of living together.

945
01:29:00,760 --> 01:29:09,120
With harmonious notes, I fulfill the urge to coexist.

946
01:29:41,360 --> 01:29:46,620
Even if I must endure the pain, I will

947
01:29:42,150 --> 01:29:43,400
Just a little more.

948
01:29:46,620 --> 01:29:51,520
sing along to the melody our two figures compose.

949
01:29:49,240 --> 01:29:49,870
Yura...

950
01:29:51,520 --> 01:29:56,730
If it can light up the hardship, then I'll face reality,

951
01:29:52,370 --> 01:29:53,830
Gobta...

952
01:29:56,730 --> 01:29:59,290
because I want to stop this spiraling chaos.

953
01:29:56,960 --> 01:30:00,090
Yura, sleep a little longer.

954
01:29:59,290 --> 01:30:06,940
I won't fall.

955
01:30:00,920 --> 01:30:05,510
The world that belongs only to us two is almost complete.

956
01:30:11,630 --> 01:30:15,100
Striking down my own cowardice,

957
01:30:14,060 --> 01:30:15,100
I can hear it.

958
01:30:15,100 --> 01:30:18,860
if I have the courage to raise my well-honed fist against the trial, it's fine even if I get hurt.

959
01:30:17,600 --> 01:30:18,860
It's right there.

960
01:30:18,860 --> 01:30:21,000
I know what it means to be strong.

961
01:30:21,000 --> 01:30:25,120
When the moment comes, I'll be ready.

962
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:27,990
Before I fade away, I make a firm vow:

963
01:30:25,740 --> 01:30:27,820
You have to make it in time, Gobta.

964
01:30:27,990 --> 01:30:29,980
to protect you.

965
01:30:28,450 --> 01:30:30,740
I'm coming right now.

966
01:30:29,980 --> 01:30:37,420
Don't wound my heart or body, and I can coexist with you.

967
01:30:36,790 --> 01:30:39,290
Go!

968
01:30:42,840 --> 01:30:44,710
Yura!

969
01:30:49,090 --> 01:30:50,350
Yura!

970
01:30:58,270 --> 01:31:01,810
Yura, I really like you!

971
01:31:03,210 --> 01:31:05,360
Gobta!

972
01:31:09,450 --> 01:31:13,300
Striking down my own cowardice,

973
01:31:09,950 --> 01:31:12,240
Stay away from Yura!

974
01:31:13,300 --> 01:31:17,990
if I have the courage to raise my well-honed fist against the trial, it's fine even if I get hurt.

975
01:31:17,990 --> 01:31:19,920
I know what it means to be strong.

976
01:31:19,920 --> 01:31:23,190
When the moment comes, I'll be ready.

977
01:31:23,190 --> 01:31:27,050
Before I fade away, I make a firm vow:

978
01:31:26,010 --> 01:31:27,050
Found it.

979
01:31:27,050 --> 01:31:29,030
to protect you.

980
01:31:28,090 --> 01:31:29,130
Ray of God's Wrath!

981
01:31:29,030 --> 01:31:32,450
Don't wound my heart or body, and I can coexist with you.

982
01:31:32,450 --> 01:31:42,060
Following the shining light's guidance, I seek a radiant vision of living together.

983
01:31:42,060 --> 01:31:50,710
With harmonious notes, I fulfill the urge to coexist.

984
01:32:18,140 --> 01:32:18,910
Notice.

985
01:32:19,390 --> 01:32:22,310
The Water Dragon's wavelength has completely vanished.

986
01:32:23,980 --> 01:32:24,810
I see.

987
01:32:27,110 --> 01:32:27,800
Where's Gobta?

988
01:32:36,280 --> 01:32:37,120
Gobta!

989
01:32:41,080 --> 01:32:42,750
The Ray of God's Wrath...

990
01:32:43,370 --> 01:32:44,210
That Rimuru.

991
01:32:44,830 --> 01:32:47,960
Just how much computational power must that take?

992
01:32:51,510 --> 01:32:54,780
I'd better prepare a delicious breakfast for everyone.

993
01:33:02,140 --> 01:33:04,650
Lord Rimuru, Gobta.

994
01:33:05,690 --> 01:33:06,520
Thank you both.

995
01:33:08,190 --> 01:33:10,490
Now the Kingdom of Kaien is saved.

996
01:33:13,400 --> 01:33:16,300
What happened to the Water Dragon in the end?

997
01:33:19,040 --> 01:33:22,160
This time... it has perished completely.

998
01:33:25,010 --> 01:33:25,810
Yura...

999
01:33:44,890 --> 01:33:45,730
Yura.

1000
01:33:48,860 --> 01:33:51,050
I like you.

1001
01:33:53,240 --> 01:33:53,860
If...

1002
01:33:55,110 --> 01:33:57,820
If you'd be willing...

1003
01:33:59,700 --> 01:34:01,990
I'd like to stay in the Kingdom of Kaien.

1004
01:34:03,250 --> 01:34:05,960
I want to stay here and help you.

1005
01:34:07,000 --> 01:34:08,770
And live on together with you.

1006
01:34:14,510 --> 01:34:15,760
Don't get ahead of yourself.

1007
01:34:19,510 --> 01:34:20,970
I'm truly grateful to you.

1008
01:34:22,220 --> 01:34:25,710
But beyond that, I feel nothing for you.

1009
01:34:35,990 --> 01:34:40,160
From now on, our nation will surely establish ties with Tempest and other countries.

1010
01:34:40,990 --> 01:34:44,540
I merely used you for that purpose, that's all.

1011
01:34:47,040 --> 01:34:50,380
I have no intention whatsoever of living with you.

1012
01:34:53,090 --> 01:34:54,130
Yura...

1013
01:34:56,420 --> 01:34:57,260
Gobta.

1014
01:34:59,140 --> 01:35:03,930
Next time, don't be fooled by a wicked woman like me.

1015
01:35:04,290 --> 01:35:05,180
Yura!

1016
01:35:12,060 --> 01:35:13,110
Yura...

1017
01:35:20,410 --> 01:35:21,760
Shot down.

1018
01:35:22,070 --> 01:35:25,620
A woman's heart is deeper than the sea.

1019
01:35:26,040 --> 01:35:27,710
This is perfectly normal.

1020
01:35:28,120 --> 01:35:29,850
Lord Rimuru...

1021
01:35:30,210 --> 01:35:31,460
That's right, Gobta.

1022
01:35:31,670 --> 01:35:34,170
If you've got any problems, just ask Lord Rimuru.

1023
01:35:34,170 --> 01:35:36,260
She's putting words in my mouth again.

1024
01:35:36,460 --> 01:35:37,300
Is that so?

1025
01:35:38,340 --> 01:35:40,430
Don't look at me with those eyes.

1026
01:35:42,090 --> 01:35:43,760
I'll follow you forever.

1027
01:35:44,390 --> 01:35:45,850
Hold on.

1028
01:35:45,850 --> 01:35:48,980
It's fine—he's Lord Rimuru, after all.

1029
01:35:48,980 --> 01:35:51,270
There's something I'd like to ask you right now.

1030
01:35:51,270 --> 01:35:53,560
Uh, hold on a second.

1031
01:35:56,280 --> 01:35:58,990
Our nation has lost the Water Dragon's protection.

1032
01:35:59,400 --> 01:36:02,740
From now on, we're bound to face many hardships.

1033
01:36:02,950 --> 01:36:06,700
With the priestess's support, we'll guide the people together.

1034
01:36:06,700 --> 01:36:07,640
Yes.

1035
01:36:09,000 --> 01:36:12,120
Where did Yura go? Why isn't she here?

1036
01:36:13,380 --> 01:36:17,960
Even though Lady Yura has finally freed herself from the bonds of her family's bloodline...

1037
01:36:19,010 --> 01:36:20,880
she still won't show herself.

1038
01:36:41,530 --> 01:36:44,030
Please watch over the Kingdom of Kaien as it moves toward the future.

1039
01:37:10,520 --> 01:37:13,640
Thank you, but it's no longer needed.

1040
01:37:22,190 --> 01:37:24,910
I'm sorry, Gobta.

1041
01:37:26,160 --> 01:37:30,120
Back then, I understood everything.

1042
01:37:32,620 --> 01:37:34,290
Our family always believed

1043
01:37:34,710 --> 01:37:38,670
that the flute was given to us by the Water Dragon's messenger.

1044
01:37:42,210 --> 01:37:43,260
But that wasn't so.

1045
01:37:45,340 --> 01:37:48,470
In truth, I myself am the heart of the Water Dragon.

1046
01:37:49,930 --> 01:37:52,850
For ages, I've gone through reincarnation after reincarnation.

1047
01:37:57,230 --> 01:38:00,980
I'm sorry, Gobta.

1048
01:38:04,470 --> 01:38:05,990
Hearing those words of yours,

1049
01:38:08,070 --> 01:38:11,620
I was actually happy.

1050
01:38:15,160 --> 01:38:17,880
I really wish I could meet you again.

1051
01:38:37,900 --> 01:38:38,520
Notice.

1052
01:38:38,730 --> 01:38:41,650
The individual designated Yura's reaction has disappeared.

1053
01:38:42,690 --> 01:38:43,530
I see.

1054
01:38:46,030 --> 01:38:48,340
Yura will surely return someday.

1055
01:38:49,160 --> 01:38:50,410
You sensed it?

1056
01:38:51,240 --> 01:38:52,910
Just a faint feeling.

1057
01:38:58,750 --> 01:39:03,510
When the clock strikes two in the morning, the journey will begin.

1058
01:39:03,510 --> 01:39:08,270
Along the hazy route, I'll reach straight into the depths of your heart.

1059
01:43:27,980 --> 01:43:30,060
Now do you understand your own limits?

1060
01:43:31,110 --> 01:43:35,800
I'll come for you again—be ready before then.

1061
01:43:36,530 --> 01:43:40,070
And fix that arrogant attitude of yours.

1062
01:43:42,990 --> 01:43:45,290
A slime Demon Lord?

1063
01:43:47,160 --> 01:43:49,670
This might be even more fun than toying with Leon.

1064
01:43:56,130 --> 01:43:57,380
So you lost.

1065
01:43:57,380 --> 01:43:58,420
I didn't lose.

1066
01:43:58,840 --> 01:44:00,030
There's always next time.

1067
01:44:00,510 --> 01:44:02,390
I said I didn't lose!

1068
01:44:04,890 --> 01:44:08,850
It seems this boring stretch of time is about to end.
